<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=684157409&t=artid%3d57133fe3-e87f-437c-815b-0a2614a24a73%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=684157409&t=artid%3d57133fe3-e87f-437c-815b-0a2614a24a73%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" border="0" alt=""></a>They were arrested on Saturday afternoon for possessing a stolen firearm outside the venue.  It was reported that members of the Mpumalanga Amaberete received information that some people were playing with a firearm in the parking area opposite Gate 6. Amaberete members found the six men in a Quantum taxi with North West registration plates.  They searched the men, who were allegedly all drinking, but found nothing on them. But they found a Norinco 213 pistol with five rounds of live ammunition in the vehicle. It was later established that it had been stolen in Pinetown, KZN. The suspects were arrested and detained at Booysens Police Station. National police spokesman Brigadier Vishnu Naidoo said the arrests took place outside the premises in the parking lot.  “Police officers were conducting patrols and suspected the men of drinking alcohol.  “They conducted a search and found a pistol, ” said Naidoo. “It was later established that the firearm had been reported stolen in the Pinetown. The six are charged with unlawful possession of a firearm and ammunition.” 
